Los Angeles Rams center Brian Allen has tested positive for COVID-19, a team spokesperson confirmed to USA TODAY Sports.
Allen is the first known active NFL player to test positive for COVID-19.
Allen first tested positive for the novel coronavirus three weeks ago, reported Fox's Jay Glazer.
An unknown member of the Los Angeles Chargers has tested positive for COVID-19 and two other members of the organization also have shown symptoms, according to ESPN's Adam Schefter.
In late March, a SoFi Stadium construction worker tested positive for COVID-19.